Sisko (sp) in Bjarken need fragments of the Tuscaran Glacier map. The 5 parts of the maps are guarded by giant warriors just outside the Glacier entrance, in Delling's Crater. Kill hrimthursa (sp ?) warriors until the 5 parts of the map drop (they don't drop it every time, you may have to kill a bit more than 5 giants). Come back to the quest giver in Bjarken, who will ask you to bring back a Griffon Frostwing eye. The eye must be used as a lens to decipher the maps. Frostwings can be found in the various Aeries in Delling's Crater.<br>
Bring back the eye to get your reward, a crush12%, body12% hits21 jewel slot item.<br>
I think the level requirement for this quest is at least 45, maybe more, considereing the mobs you have to fight.<br>
<br>
A more complex mid level quest (I think minimal level around 25-30). Sinna Redtoes in Aegirhamm had her maps stolen by thieves supposedly from the Grenlock clan. She tells you to ask the local head of the Clan in Aegir (who just happen to be 50 ft near her <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ). <br>
She tells you that four members of the clan have fled Aegir's landing, possibly because of a theft, and fled to Knarr. She gives you a ticket to knarr, to investigate. In knarr, ask the local guards until you find the npc who has seen the thieves. He will tell you that a man named Modolf bought his boat and fled to the east, but died to a violent storm in a shipwreck. He'll explain (look at your journal) where to find his remains. The description in the journal is pretty accurate, so I won't transcript it here. When you kill Modolf, he drops a map, and a note.<br>
The note leads you to the city of Bjarken, when one of the 3 remaining thieves is located, and includes a horse ticket.<br>
In Bjarken, the woman tells you the 2 other thieves headed east, then north with the map, but have been caught in an avalanche. Now they were tricky to fight, and I spent a lot of time before stumbling into them, at loc 23k 48k : 2 zombies with the name of the two now deceased thieves.<br>
Bring back the two fragment of the map dropped by the undead to the redeemed thief in Bjarken, then head back to Sinna in Aegir to give her the two maps (Modolf's and the now completed one).<br>
She gives you a varied choice of jewelry : just click on each reward's name to see her comments, then proceed through the dialogue when your mind is set.<br>
I took the reward which sounded the more skald-ish, of course <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :hat --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/pimp.gif ALT=":hat"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Luminous citrine pin : charisma6 strength6 heat4% hits6, jewel slot level 29 item, not too shabby considering I replaced Nimh's curse with the Daemon DF jewel well into my 40ies <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
